ntent/uploads/2022/01/MTN-768x311.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />BofA highlighted MTN and Airtel Africa in the Telecoms sector. MTN was one of the standout performers on the JSE in 2021, advancing some 180% over a 12 month period. Gold Fields <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-553262" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/GoldFields.png" alt="" width="766" height="319" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/GoldFields.png 766w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/GoldFields-300x125.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />  BofA said that at 50% of demand for most mined commodities, China looms large in its thinking. “A hard landing is not our base case, but we are wary of potential risks related to property,” it said. The bank also put buy tags on Anglo American (volume growth, self-help, PGMs, Diamonds), Glencore (copper, coal), South32 (Aluminium). Read: The biggest risks to stocks in 2022 – and where people plan to invest